						               													<description>The game allows to study and recreate the most dramatic battle in the Alps front during WW1, a struggle that, due to italian High Commands unpreparedness, evolved in one of the worse disaster in the whole italian military history.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Compared to other offensives of the same period, where territotial gains were measured in meters or little more, often paid with appalling losses from both sides, the austro-german operation &amp;ldquo;Waffentreue&amp;rdquo; (Loyalty of arms) pushed back the whole italian front for 150 kilometers in few days.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;But, after a loss of 300.000 casualties (most of them prisoners) and 1300 guns, Italy made a fierce, desperate resistance on the Piave river, and managed to snatch the victory from the jaws of the defeat.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Components:&amp;#10;2 maps 60 x 85; &amp;#10;400+ counters; &amp;#10;4 player aid cards; &amp;#10;a 20 pages rules booklet&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Scale:&amp;#10;Every day is divided in two turns. The first day has one more preparatory phase. &amp;#10;An hexagon on the map corresponds to about 1000 meters. &amp;#10;The unit counters represent infantry battalions/regiments and minor units&amp;#10;&amp;#10;COMPLEXITY&amp;#10;3/5&amp;#10;&amp;#10;SOLITAIRE SUITABILITY&amp;#10;2/5&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
